==Trivia==
*In the comics, '''Kingo Sunen''' came from a [[Japan|Japanese]] settlement and learned the ways of the samurai. When hiding among [[humans]], he was an action film star who played samurai.

==Behind the Scenes==
*[[Kumail Nanjiani]] has stated that he played Kingo by combining the wisecracking attitude of {{WPS|John McClane}} from ''{{WPS|Die Hard (film series)|Die Hard}}'' and the look of {{WPS|Bollywood}} actor {{WPS|Hrithik Roshan}}.<ref>[https://www.menshealth.com/entertainment/a31229858/kumail-nanjiani-marvel-eternals/ Kumail Nanjiani Says John McClane Inspired His Marvel ‘Eternals’ Character]</ref>
*[[Anton Simpson-Tidy]] and [[Bryan McCoy]] were stunt doubles for [[Kumail Nanjiani]] in the role of Kingo.
*[[Ketan Majmudar]] was a stand-in and a photo double for [[Kumail Nanjiani]] in the role of Kingo.
*[[Jeremy Slater]] revealed that in early script of ''[[Moon Knight (TV series)|Moon Knight]]'', Kingo and a few other Eternals was supposed to appear in a flashback sequence in Ancient [[Egypt]]. They would have fought alongside [[Khonshu]]'s Avatar against [[Ammit]] and her Avatar. The idea was scrapped due to the expenditure.<ref>[https://thedirect.com/article/moon-knight-eternals-cameos-exclusive Moon Knight Producer Reveals Eternals' Scrapped Cameos (Exclusive)]</ref>

